== Garlic Rice ==

Boil a half-full #kettle{}. Peel and grate the @garlic cloves{3}(peeled and grated) using a #garlic press{}.

Heat the @oil{½%tbsp} in a deep #saucepan{} on medium heat. Once hot, add half the garlic and cook for ~{30%seconds}.

Stir in the @basmati rice{150%g} and cook until coated, ~{1%minute}. Add @salt{¼%tsp} and the boiled water and cook for ~{10-12%minutes}.

Once cooked, drain in a #sieve{} and pop back in the pan. Cover with a #lid{} and leave to the side until ready to serve.

== Chicken Korma ==

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a large #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the @diced British chicken breast{1%pack} to the pan and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}.

Cook until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}. Turn occasionally.

> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

Add the @tomato puree{30%g}, @korma curry paste{50%g} and remaining garlic to the pan. Cook until fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Add the @chicken stock paste{10%g} and @water{150%ml}(for the sauce). Bring to the boil, then lower the heat to medium and cover with a lid.

Simmer until the chicken is cooked and the sauce has thickened, ~{5-6%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Remove the lid from the curry and stir through the @creme fraiche{75%g} and @honey{1%tbsp}.

Bring to the boil, then add the @baby spinach{40%g} to the pan a handful at a time until wilted and piping hot, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Remove from the heat.

== Finishing ==

Fluff the rice up with a #fork{} and stir through the @butter{20%g}.

Taste the curry, and season with salt and pepper if needed.

Share the rice between your #bowls{}.

Top with the chicken korma.

Sprinkle over the @toasted flaked almonds{15%g} to finish.

Enjoy!